social_posts.post_text: A successful opening night here in Sydney with the beautiful cast and (some) of the creatives behind @madagascarmusicalaus. Sydney, Melbourne and Perth, hope you’re ready for us! 🦁
This years Christmas wrapping theme 😍🎁
Merry Christmas from the Papas’ ❤️
Day in the life…on tour 🦁
You are the sum of who you surround yourself with, and I just spent 10 weeks with some pretty great people. Missing you all 🥹❤️

Happy 2nd birthday to my favourite little man. I can’t even begin to explain how much I love you. It’s only been two short years and we’ve still got the rest of our lives together, I can’t wait. You make our lives so much better Bastian, and I hope you never get sick of dressing the same as me 😍❤️
I remember this one time, we went out…🕺💃

I’m taking Dad-ing to the next level with the Ferrari of strollers, the Olive by @edwardsandcobaby Taking both our little kiddies out and about has never looked so good, or been so easy. Wheelie couldn’t do without it! 😉

After a gruelling tour, and doing this character makeup 95 times, its fair to say my skin is in desperate need of a little TLC, so I’m visiting the good people at @clearskincareclinics_nz for a bit of a skin reset. Today I’m having one of my favorite treatments, skin needling. It works by making thousands of micro-punctures on the skin, lifting and firming, improving skin tone and smoothing away fine lines and acne scars. Overall it’s a great reset after the hell I’ve just put my skin through.
Practicing our smizing for next weeks Vogue shoot…

We are what we drink…
Her: fruity and delicious 🍓
Me: dark, bitter and a little fluffy 🧁
One of my favourite things to do is getting ice cream with my little guy. I just love his attitude towards life, so much. He’s always happy and everything’s a good time 🍦😍

It’s his third Easter but it’s the first time he’s ever grasped the concept of an Easter Egg hunt. It was so sweet watching him find little treasures with his cousin, can’t wait till Aiya can join in, and not just get a toy in the face 😂

I’m stoked to finally share this exciting news with you all. I’m joining @thetentenors and we’ll be touring New Zealand (April) and Australia (June and July). Hit the link in bio for ticket details 🙂🖤
Day in the life on tour with @thetentenors 🎶🎙️

Ten Tenors in ten cities! Thanks to everyone who came out and watched the show around NZ, and thanks to the guys for making my debut with the group a memorable one. Can’t wait to kick it all off again in Australia @thetentenors
Took the little squirts to see Barbara and Peter 🦖🦖
Birthday dinners and blurry pictures 😍

Curls get the girls! Not an add, I just really appreciate a good barber. If you’re after a new barber and happen to be in Auckland, check out my guy @renscuts he won’t disappoint! Been getting my fortnightly trims with him for 3 years now. Now cutting at @nexus_barbershop_westgate

Happy birthday wifey, another year older and more beautiful than ever. 
You’re my favourite person and I still feel so lucky and proud to call you my wife. We’ve done so many amazing things together, but we’ve also faced a few challenges in our time. Creating special moments with you will always come naturally, but there’s nothing more reassuring than also knowing you’re the one I’ll be sharing life’s challenges with.

You’re such a beautiful person inside and out, and I’m so proud of the person you are. You’re an incredible mother and we’re so lucky to have you in our little family. Although Bastian and Aiya are only little and love you very much, I can’t wait till they’re old enough to really understand just how incredible you are. 

Happy birthday my love, I love you ❤️
What a special moment having Bastian sing “happy birthday” to his mum….and his sister Aiya and himself 😂🥳🎂
Important business meeting stuff with a very important businessman ☕️❤️😍
My beige babe 🤍 @meganlouisepapas

Winter sucks, you can’t have dinner time picnics outside, it’s too cold, and it gets dark so bloody early! So we thought we’d switch up the routine for Friday night, and treat Basty to Fish n Chips in the lounge. He even helped clean up… sort of.
Me after getting the reminder email that tomorrows dress up day 😅💙🧡

So @jonoandben tasked me with making something out of this giant ass carrot Jono found at the supermarket. Obviously, I’m not the baker in the fam, so Andrew has come to the rescue. We’re making a carrot and pineapple cake, with cream cheese icing, and pineapple flowers! 
Follow along to see how it’s made, and see the reveal to the boys at the end. 
Also recipe below in case you wanna try it!  We didn’t even use the whole carrot! 

4 eggs 2 cups white sugar 1¼ cups vegetable oil 2 cups plain white flour 1½ teaspoons baking powder 2 teaspoons baking soda 2 teaspoons cinnamon 1 teaspoon mixed spice 2½ cups grated carrot 1 cup pineapple pieces 1 cup walnuts piece   Icing 150g cream cheese, room temperature 150g butter, room temperature 21/2 cups Icing Sugar Zest of one lemon
How lucky am I to live these moments with my little people 😍❤️

We’re back baking! This time we have heaps of lemons at home so Andrew’s whipping up some Baked Lemon and Poppyseed Donuts! 
Let us know if there’s something you’d like to see us make, or if there’s an ingredient you’d like us to make something with! 

Ingredients:
1 cup plain flour
1 teaspoon baking powder
1/4 teaspoon baking soda
1 Tablespoon poppy seeds
1/2 cup milk
2 Tablespoons butter, melted
1 egg
1/3 cup sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla essence 
1 Tablespoon lemon juice
1 Tablespoon lemon zest

For the glaze:
1 cup icing sugar
lemon zest
3 Tablespoon lemon juice
1 teaspoon vanilla essence 
Milk (for thinning)
Last night before I head to Brazil and managed to squeeze in a dinner date with my babe ❤️😍
Brazilian cuisine with a twist at @dalvaedito before we leave São Paulo tomorrow, and head to Belo Horizonte for our first Tenors show.
Performed on @maisvocefcoficial here in Brazil today. Not gonna lie meeting @anamariabragaoficial was pretty special but meeting @louromaneofc was the real treat! 🦜
What a treat performing on Brazils @maisvocefcoficial today and meeting the very lovely @anamariabragaoficial ❤️🦜🇧🇷
Spent the day in Rio with 500 of my closest friends checking out the statue of Christ the Redeemer, and all of us trying to squeeze into one photo. Besties! 🤪
Not sure if I was there to take a photo of 500 strangers or of this ginormous statue. Either way…remember to take your sunglasses, it’s glary AF up there!

One of those pinch me moments I’ll never forget. I think 11 year old Andrew would be pretty stoked with himself if he knew he’d get the opportunity to perform at this beautiful theatre, here in Rio. This is one for the books 🤍
Objects are closer than they appear 👀

AD- 🍔 Elevate your meal game with @angelbaynz 😋 Convenient, nutritious, and delicious – find them at your local supermarket. 🛒 Visit angelbay.co.nz for recipes and follow them on Instagram/Facebook for inspiration. 😍 Stock up for those busy nights, Angel Bay’s got your back! 🙌

One whole year today with our gorgeous little girl, Aiya! 🥳🎂You have the most incredible little personality  and I can’t wait to keep getting to know you as we grow together, and getting to do all the things girl dads get to do with their daughters. I’m one very proud and very mushy dad today 🥹❤️

Had the most incredible long weekend celebrating our little girl, Aiya’s 1st birthday. Such a great feeling being surrounded by our family and friends, soaking up the sun and watching the kiddies have the best time. Ad - thank you to the amazing folks at @thegoodparty.co for the incredible soft play set up and balloon backdrop. The kids wouldn’t have had half the fun without it. And that beautiful (and delicious) cake was made by @sweetbitesnz if you’ve followed me for a while you’ll know we literally only get their cakes, that’s because they look so damn good and taste even better! My heart (and stomach) is full 😍❤️
Living my best big kid life setting up this frozen, sea creatures sensory activity for Aiya’s 1st birthday. Not sure who had more fun 🧊🐳🦞🦈🦭

What an incredible weekend away with a group of friends, who I’ve known for half my life! We celebrated  our dear friend Jacky’s 30th birthday with great food, great laughs, great company and a killer cocktail evening where each couple was tasked with making a cocktail…I think we were meant to pick a winner but we got distracted by the draaaanks 🤪

What a delicious night celebrating our TorTor’s 30th birthday. What started out as a working relationship helping us with our kiddies has turned into such a special friendship. Thanks for being part of our family @victorianewport ❤️

Santa if you’re reading this, those last two are my favourites! 🥸 Ad - Got an exclusive first look at the new @specsaversnewzealand 2023 summer range, featuring eyewear from Marc Jacobs, Collette Dinnigan, Mimco, Deus and more…it was “spec-tacular” to say the least! 😎

Ad/ - We’re back in the kitchen, this time creating a five layer dip to pair with the delicious new Long Beach Classics Tortilla Strips! They come in three flavours, Rosemary & Sea Salt, Tomato & Basil and Dairy-Free Cheese. They are entirely vegan, gluten free, and available now at major supermarkets nationwide! Ready, set, dip! @longbeachclassicsnz #LongBeachClassics #snacktime #nzfood #chipsanddip #vegannz #glutenfreenz #newzealand
“We are the music makers, and we are the dreamers of the dreams” 🍫🍭
Just two boys out on the town, in their pink shirts, rocking out to their favourite @emmamemmamemma tunes 🎟️🧡
Make a margarita with me - AD @josecuervo_nz
So random this old guy in red wanted to take a picture with us, but hey, it’s Christmas and why ruin his day. Merry Christmas everyone! ❤️
Happy new year everyone! Spent the night with my favourite people throwing back cocktails…and cheeseburgers, into the early hours 🍔🥂🍾
Our annual visit to the strawberry field to eat our body weight in berries and ice cream 🤤🍓😍

Today I celebrate six years of marriage with my partner in crime. Thank you for continuing to make my time on this earth a good time, and for joining me in feeling out numbered by our two little munchkins. I love you my sweetheart, you deserve a medal for putting up with my pedanticism ❤️😍
When you go to the beach with kids, you get sand in places you never imagined 😳😅
